ShadowQuest

Class Unit

  • java.lang.Object
    • ShadowQuest.GameObject
      • ShadowQuest.Unit
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Monster, Player, Villager

    public abstract class Unit
extends GameObject
    Units in general represent humans in the game world Most units can move, and all units interact with the player in some way. All units have stats.
    Author:
    Adrian Cheung

      • renderLabel

        public void renderLabel(org.newdawn.slick.Graphics g,
                        Camera camera)
        Render the unit's label, which displays the name of the unit as well as the current Health of the unit. The label is rendered a small distance above the image of the unit.
        Parameters:
        g: - Slick graphics object, used for drawing
        camera: - Camera, displays the game world

      • update

        public abstract void update(double dir_x,
                            double dir_y,
                            double a_on,
                            double t_on,
                            int delta,
                            World world)
                     throws org.newdawn.slick.SlickException
        Update method takes user input for controlling the Player character and translates this into some in-game event. The update is done many times per second. The delta parameter is used to standardise gameplay across systems of differing performance.
        Parameters:
        dir_x: - User input flag for horizontal movement: move left if negative, right if positive, don't move if zero
        dir_y: - User input flag for vertical movement; same as above
        a_on: - User input flag for attack
        t_on: - User input flag for interact
        delta: - Number of milliseconds since last update
        world: - World in which updates are taking place
        Throws:
        org.newdawn.slick.SlickException - General exception thrown by Slick library classes
